action was inspired by the withdrawal from the Paris agreement.) In 2022 in Qatar, timed for the World Cup, he is planning, as he calls it, the largest art installation incorporating artificial intelligence that has ever happened. There was near pandemonium from selfie-takers around Comedian in Miami, and when Datuna saw it (and saw it was from Cattelan) he thought it was great. But when he Googled it and saw the asking price it took â€œabout 15 or 20 minutesâ€ to conceive of â€œthe answer I must give to him and to the art worldâ€. â€œWarhol put banana on a canvas,â€ Datuna says with his Georgian accent. â€œCattelan takes a real banana and puts it on the wall. David took banana from the wall and ate it!â€ Datuna called his performance piece Hungry Artist and it quickly went viral. He did not have permission from Cattelan or the Perrotin Gallery. â€œHungry Artistâ€ Art performance by me ğŸ™‚ I love Maurizio Cattelan artwork and I really love this installation Itâ€™s very delicious ğŸ™‚ #artbasel #artbaselmiamibeach #daviddatuna #Eatingabanana #Mauriziocattelan #Hungryartist @kiwi.artsgroup A post shared by  David Datuna (@david_datuna) on Dec 7, 2019 at 11:38am PST Below is a further transcript of our phone conversation, edited for clarity. Have you met Maurizio Cattelan? No, but I follow him, he is a great artist. Has he reached out to you since this past weekend? No. Itâ€™s plausible you will meet him some day on the contemporary art circuit, though. Would it be a warm meeting? I would love to meet him. I think he is a genius. Art is about comedy, about fun, about tragedy, about emotions. He played this very well. I love the banana of Andy Warhol, but I think Cattelan has put the banana on a different level. What I donâ€™t like, however, is that a banana costs 20 cents. I think it is a good idea to put it in a museum if it is free to watch. But when you sell it for $120,000? Then decide to make a second and third edition, and that third edition is $150,000? It is s